						<summary>

						<p>This is engraved below No. 1, and is in faulty and later characters. It is dated in the 13th year of Rājarājakēsarivarman (Rājarāja I) the victor of Kāndaḷūr-śālai, and records a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> as endowment for the daily supply of an <hi rend="italic">āḻākku</hi> of ghee for burning a lamp in the temple, made by a lady named Atimāndurai a resident of Ilachchikkuḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vīrāpuram in Miḻalai-nāḍu on the northern bank.</p>						

						</summary>
